Syrian Foreign Minister Walid Muallem said on Monday his country would reject any United Nations role in monitoring the implementation of four &#8220;de-escalation&#8221; zones.&#8220;We do not accept a role for the United Nations or international forces to monitor the agreement,&#8221; Muallem told reporters in Damascus.Regime backers Russia and Iran and rebel supporter Turkey reached a deal on Thursday on four &#8220;de-escalation zones&#8221; in Syria where the government and opposition will halt hostilities.-AFP